HEADWORD: Magniloquent
<hw>Mag*nil"o*quent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>magnus</ets> great + <ets>loquens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr.
of <ets>loqui</ets> to speak. See <er>Magnitude</er>,
<er>Loquacious</er>.]</ety> <def>Speaking pompously; using swelling
discourse; bombastic; tumid in style; grandiloquent.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Mag*nil"o*quent*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magniloquous</ent>⟦br⟧
